  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Protection for older people in Donbas (in consortia with Mercy Corps)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Community volunteers will be trained and equipped to provide recreational activities for Older Persons</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Community volunteers will regularly report back to social work professional on vulnerabilities of older people in their areas of responsibility in order to be aware of needs and ensure they are met, including on health, shelter, psychosocial factors, as well as protection risks (threats, abuse, harassment, discrimination, isolation</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Community volunteers will visit vulnerable and isolated older people at home to help with household chores and provide companionship</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ensuring vulnerable older people are on relief distribution lists of other humanitarian agencies for food, Non-Food Items and other distributions</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing mobility aids where necessary, including wheelchairs, hearing aids, walking sticks, glasses</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing psychosocial support, basic home-based care and referrals to health services to 4,500 vulnerable older people through social work professionals and community volunteers (CVs) (typically aged 50-65)</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Working as part of a consortia, HelpAge specially will lead the protection component of the programme focussing on psychosocial and referral support, and basic home-care to the most vulnerable older people (OP), over 65 years old, and strengthen overall community coping capacities. In addition, HelpAge will supply specific needs materials and build up awareness of older people sensitive programming among other consortia partners.</narrative>
  </description>
